description:
Under certain circumstances, the code assist feature in the IDE is replacing more code than expected. The following is an example class where the issue occurs:

public class X {
  void bar(X x) {
    baz(x.foo());
  }

  int foo() {
    return 5;
  }

  void baz(int i, int j) {
  }
}

To reproduce the issue, follow these steps:

1. Create an instance of X, say x.
2. Call x.bar(x) method.
The code assist should replace the code 'baz(x.foo());' with 'baz(x.foo();x.foo());'. However, it is currently replacing it with 'baz(x.foo().foo());'.

Expected Behavior:

The code assist should replace 'baz(x.foo());' with 'baz(x.foo();x.foo());'.

Additional Information:

The code assist option to control the amount of source code to replace was added in a previous version but has been removed.
